CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 25, 1953, pg. 11 reads: "United In Catholic Rites - Lieut. and Mrs. Robert Joseph Cameron are shown leaving the altar in Church of Our Lady of the Blessed Sacrament in Pittsburgh, Pa., where they were united in marriage. The bride is the former Miss Jacqueline Peeler, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Melvin Eugene Peeler of Bricelyn Street, who gave a sparkling party following the ritual, on the Peeler lawn, where a specially constructed patio made a handsome setting for the many guests. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bride Jacqueline Peeler Cameron wearing gown with sheer floral overlay and matching veil, and groom Lieutenant Robert Joseph Cameron wearing U.S. Army uniform, walking down aisle in Church of Our Lady of the Blessed Sacrament
